Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
timing_use_clo...ck_net_marking(25.10)  timing_use_clo...ck_net_marking(25.10)

Name
       timing_use_clock_pin_attribute_for_clock_net_marking

Syntax
       timing_use_clock_pin_attribute_for_clock_net_marking

       {true | false}

       Default: false

       Allows  the  software to use clock pin attribute settings for clock net
       marking.

       The timing system determines which nets are recognized as clock nets by
       considering different heuristics - including having an upstream path to
       clock sources and a downstream path to clock targets.

       When set to true, the pins that have the Liberty timing library pin at-
       tribute setting `clock:true' will be interpreted  as  additional  clock
       targets for the clock marking algorithm.

       When  set to false, the set of clock targets includes pins that are the
       launching point for sequential paths or are the reference pin  for  se-
       quential timing checks - typically register clock pins.

       To set this global variable, use the set command.

